abstractText: Natural Origin Spawner Abundance or NOSA is a Viable Salmonid Population (VSP) indicator that is used to inform NOAA management decisions.The Interior Columbia Technical Review Team (ICTRT) uses theVSPindicators to assess the current status of the populations in terms of extinction risk (ICTRT 2010).
title: Natural Origin Spawner Abundance (NOSA) Calculation v1.0
